00:36:02,950 --> 00:36:12,640
balanced approach. As I said earlier, we recognise
that the majority of individuals who suffered

396
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:14,589
did so at the hands of terrorists.

397
00:36:14,589 --> 00:36:19,720
>>Andy Burnham (Leigh) (Lab): On the steps
of Downing Street, the Prime Minister pledged

398
00:36:19,720 --> 00:36:25,020
to end the “burning injustice” of so few
working-class boys going to university. Will

399
00:36:25,020 --> 00:36:31,990
she tell me how cutting every single secondary
school in Leigh, Wigan, Rochdale, Trafford

400
00:36:31,990 --> 00:36:36,560
and Manchester through her new schools funding
formula will do anything other than make that

401
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:38,119
injustice even worse?

402
00:36:38,119 --> 00:36:42,800
>>The Prime Minister: I want to ensure, through
the education system that we provide, that

403
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:47,210
there is a good school place for every child.
I am pleased to say that under Conservatives

404
00:36:47,210 --> 00:36:54,961
in government, we have seen 1.8 million more
children in good or outstanding schools. We

405
00:36:54,961 --> 00:36:59,960
are looking at the funding formula for schools
and listening to the comments that have been

406
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:06,190
made, but everyone across the House will recognise
that it has been said for some time now that

407
00:37:06,190 --> 00:37:12,481
the existing formula is not transparent or
fair. We are looking at a new formula, but

408
00:37:12,481 --> 00:37:17,049
I can assure the right hon. Gentleman that
our education policy is about ensuring that

409
00:37:17,049 --> 00:37:24,580
every child has the opportunity to go as far
as their talents and their hard work enable

410
00:37:24,580 --> 00:37:25,859
them to go.

411
00:37:25,859 --> 00:37:31,710
>>Paul Scully (Sutton and Cheam) (Con): Mr
