422
00:38:34,750 --> 00:38:41,230
It makes a huge difference to a local area
when its football club is able to progress

423
00:38:41,230 --> 00:38:45,770
to that extent, to be up there with the big
boys, and to do as well as Sutton did. I am

424
00:38:45,770 --> 00:38:49,612
also happy to congratulate Lincoln City—I
see that my hon. Friend the Member for Lincoln

425
00:38:49,612 --> 00:38:53,039
is sitting next to my hon. Friend the Member
for Sutton and Cheam (Paul Scully)—on their

426
00:38:53,039 --> 00:38:54,599
success. We wish them well for the future.

427
00:38:54,599 --> 00:38:57,190
>>Mr Speaker: Finally, I call Michelle Thomson.

428
00:38:57,190 --> 00:39:02,809
>>Michelle Thomson (Edinburgh West) (Ind):
